President Obama has nominated Judge Julie E. Carnes and Judge Gregg Jeffrey Costa to serve on the United States Courts of Appeals. Judge Carnes has been a United States District Judge in the Northern District of Georgia since 1992 and has served as Chief Judge since 2009. She has a background in law and has served in various positions within the legal system. Judge Costa is currently a United States District Judge in the Southern District of Texas. He has also held positions in the legal field and was one of the lead prosecutors in the case against R. Allen Stanford, who was convicted of committing a Ponzi scheme. Both nominees have shown dedication to public service throughout their careers.